===Verb===
{{en-verb|writes|writing|'''[[wrote]]''' ''or {{qualifier|archaic}}'' '''[[writ]]'''|'''[[written]]''' ''or {{qualifier|archaic}}'' '''[[writ]]'''}}
[[Image:Carl Friedrich Abel cropped.jpg|thumb|right|A [[w:Thomas Gainsborough|painting]] of [[w:Carl Friedrich Abel|a man]] writing.]]

# {{context|ambitransitive|lang=en}} To form letters, words or symbols on a surface in order to communicate.
#: ''The pupil '''wrote''' his name on the paper.''
#: ''Your son has been '''writing''' on the wall.''
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To be the author of (a book, article, poem, etc.).
#: ''My uncle '''writes''' newspaper articles for The Herald.''
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To send written information to.
#: (''UK'') ''Please '''write''' to me when you get there.''
#: (''US'') ''Please '''write''' me when you get there.''
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To show (information, etc) in written form.
#: ''The due day of the homework is '''written''' in the syllabus.''
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To be an author.
#: ''I '''write''' for a living.''
# {{context|transitive|computing|lang=en}} To record (data) mechanically or electronically.
#: ''The computer '''writes''' to the disk faster than it reads from it.''
# {{context|transitive|South Africa|Canada|of a form, a document, etc.|lang=en}} To [[fill in]], to [[complete]] using words.
#: ''I was very anxious to know my score after I '''wrote''' the test.''

